      "content": "I understand your frustration, and I apologize for the excessive goblin metaphors earlier; I can certainly dial that back to focus purely on the music theory mechanics you need.\n\nThe Circle of Fifths is a diagram that organizes all 12 major keys and their relative minor keys in a circle. It helps you determine key signatures by showing the relationship between keys and the number of sharps or flats they contain.\n\nHere is the pattern for the sharps:\n1.  **C Major** has no sharps.\n2.  **G Major** has 1 sharp (F#).\n3.  **D Major** has 2 sharps (F#, C#).\n4.  **A Major** has 3 sharps (F#, C#, G#).\n5.  **E Major** has 4 sharps (F#, C#, G#, D#).\n6.  **B Major** has 5 sharps (F#, C#, G#, D#, A#).\n7.  **F# Major** has 6 sharps (F#, C#, G#, D#, A#, E#).\n8.  **C# Major** has",
